1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,255
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:13,513
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,019
[Atoy] <i>I am here to save you.</i>

4
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:22,397
[Ame] <i>I really need</i>
<i>to get out of here tonight.</i>

5
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,232
<i>You need to save them too.</i>

6
00:00:24,315 --> 00:00:26,443
<i>There are many of us locked in here.</i>

7
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:27,736
PREVIOUSLY

8
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:29,404
- [Vladimir laughs]
- [clapping]

9
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:31,698
[in English] Why don't you pick
on somebody your own size?

10
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:34,409
[in English] You are a member
of the human trafficking group

11
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:35,702
Black Meridian, right?

12
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:37,996
[Atoy, in English] <i>Get out</i>
<i>of my country, you pig!</i>

13
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:39,956
- [crowd gasps]
- [grunts]

14
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,541
[crowd cheering]

15
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:44,169
[Tessie] <i>This is all because</i>
<i>of that demon customer of ours!</i>

16
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:46,504
<i>He toyed with Darryl!</i>

17
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,256
<i>He killed Darryl!</i>

18
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:51,050
[Red] <i>Did you see an old man?</i>

19
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,177
Chipper, Chipper Arenas.

20
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,179
There, sir. That is Chipper Arenas.

21
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,472
[Vladimir, in English] <i>That is not him.</i>

22
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:56,931
[in English] He is not even wearing
the same clothes.

23
00:00:57,015 --> 00:01:00,393
[grunting and groaning]

24
00:01:01,352 --> 00:01:02,687
[groans]

25
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,314
- [gun fires]
- [electricity crackles]

26
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:05,523
[Karla] <i>What is happening?</i>

27
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:07,025
[Mongki] They say
they are chasing an impostor

28
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:08,401
pretending to be a gold star member.

29
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:10,528
After I am done with you,
you will never forget this.

30
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:14,032
- [grunting and groaning]
- [alarm ringing]

31
00:01:14,115 --> 00:01:15,492
[grunting]

32
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:17,118
[Atoy] <i>They took Ame.</i>

33
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:19,204
<i>Hurry, we might not catch them.</i>

34
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:23,750
Go, go, go!

35
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,670
- [gun firing]
- [groaning]

36
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,005
[alarm ringing]

37
00:01:29,088 --> 00:01:31,090
[Lorna] You are all so stubborn, huh?

38
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:33,676
- Fine.
- All right, this way.

39
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,137
You have no shame! You killed Darryl!

40
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:37,514
- [gun fires]
- Tessie!

41
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:39,015
- [Red] Come on.
- [Lorna] You really will not stop?

42
00:01:39,098 --> 00:01:41,810
I will take you down one by one
like carnival targets.

43
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:43,478
- [Mongki] Boss, let us go!
- [man coughs]

44
00:01:43,561 --> 00:01:44,521
Come on, come on!

45
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:46,606
[coughing]

46
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,859
Let us get out of here.
We might get burned by the fire.

47
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,069
[grunting, groaning]

48
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:54,906
[car engine revving]

49
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,325
Please, please! Have mercy on me.

50
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:59,869
Let me go.

51
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:02,539
- [sobbing]
- [in English] Shut up, my little baby.

52
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,374
[in English] You are starting
to get on my nerves.

53
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:05,750
No, I do not want to.

54
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:08,419
- Let me go home to Ibyang!
- [grunts]

55
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,004
[in English] Don't be noisy!

56
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:12,632
[car engine revving]

57
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:16,761
[brazen music playing]

58
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,304
What is with that black pickup?

59
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:19,430
Why are we chasing it?

60
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:20,932
Who is this idiot?

61
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:22,725
Brother, it is a long story. Later.

62
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:24,394
[Gavin] H-hello.

63
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:25,812
[scoffs] Hello.

64
00:02:25,895 --> 00:02:27,981
[Atoy] Hurry, hurry!
Chase them. Chase them, Karla!

65
00:02:28,064 --> 00:02:31,526
[car engine revving]

66
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:38,408
[brazen music continues]

67
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:41,452
[in English] Boss,
someone is following us.

68
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:43,371
[car engine revving]

69
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:47,375
[stammers, in English] Hurry!

70
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:48,751
[in English] Go straight! Go straight!

71
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:50,879
Keep going, keep going! Go faster!

72
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:51,838
On it! On it!

73
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:58,052
[in English] What are you waiting for?!
Shoot them!

74
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,014
- [gun firing]
- [bullets plinking]

75
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,519
- [Gavin gasps]
- [Atoy groans]

76
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,776
[tires screeching]

77
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:16,779
[gun fires]

78
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:19,699
[gun fires]

79
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,118
[screaming]

80
00:03:22,201 --> 00:03:25,204
- [sobbing]
- [indistinct]

81
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:26,247
- [gun firing]
- [in English] Keep shooting!

82
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:28,082
- [tires screeching]
- [bullets plinking]

83
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,626
[Gaving gasps]

84
00:03:30,501 --> 00:03:32,337
- [gun firing]
- [Gavin] Hey!

85
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:36,633
- [car engine revving]
- [intense music playing]

86
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:39,469
[in English] This is all your fault!

87
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:42,805
- What is this?! Let me go!
- [in English] Out!

88
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,557
- [Vladimir, in English] Get out!
- [Ame] Let me go!

89
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:47,769
[suave music playing]

90
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:49,687
[engine whirring]

91
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,647
[sewing machine whirring]

92
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:51,606
[swishing]

93
00:03:51,689 --> 00:03:52,565
[snipping]

94
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,069
[sewing machine whirring]

95
00:03:56,152 --> 00:03:57,487
[sewing machine whirring]

96
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:58,279
[gun cocks]

97
00:03:58,363 --> 00:03:59,906
- [gun firing]
- [thudding]

98
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:00,865
[explosion]

99
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:03,159
[clicking]

100
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,245
[snips]

101
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,331
[electronic blipping]

102
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:13,336
‪[Tonet inhales]

103
00:04:16,547 --> 00:04:17,757
[Tonet sighs]

104
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:21,052
Until now, there is still no word
from Brother and Karla.

105
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,304
Do you know where they auditioned?

106
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,974
[in English] Uh… Audition?

107
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:28,977
Did Master tell you that?

108
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:32,563
Yes. That is why they asked me
to do makeup, right?

109
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:38,403
Why, Ibyang, did they not audition?

110
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:43,032
Uh, please just pray with me for them.

111
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,077
All right.

112
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:53,376
[solemn music playing]

113
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:58,673
[in English] In the name of the Father,

114
00:04:58,756 --> 00:05:02,427
the Son, the Holy Spirit. Amen.

115
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,263
[in English] Oh, Heavenly Father,

116
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,681
please watch over--

117
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:09,642
Oh, wow, the prayer is in English.

118
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,227
How fancy of you.

119
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:15,189
They taught us at the orphanage.

120
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:16,316
Shall I continue?

121
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,318
- Oh.
- Do you have another question?

122
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,570
Sorry. Please continue.

123
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,656
[in English] Oh, Heavenly Father,

124
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:25,366
please watch over Sister Ame

125
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:28,745
- and Master Grumpy on their journey,
- [Tonet mutters]

126
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:31,539
and please keep them safe from harm's way.

127
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:35,001
Come closer. Come even closer.

128
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:38,629
- [intense music playing]
- [screams]

129
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,506
[in English] Protect their steps,

130
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:41,883
guide their path,

131
00:05:41,966 --> 00:05:44,177
and bring them home safely.

132
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,638
[intense music continues]

133
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:52,518
‪[indistinct]

134
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:55,521
[dreamy music playing]

135
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:56,981
Are you okay?

136
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:05,448
[in English] May your peace be with them
until they arrive.

137
00:06:06,115 --> 00:06:07,575
[in English] Amen.

138
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:08,785
[in English] Amen, Papa Jesus!

139
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:11,746
Please, please,
just bring them back to us safely.

140
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:13,581
[in English] Please, please,
please, Papa Jesus. Amen.

141
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:19,253
Uh, Sister Tonet,
I am done with my prayer.

142
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,464
Uh… Amen.

143
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,968
In the name of the Father,
the Son, the Holy Spirit. Amen.

144
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:31,641
- [hopeful music playing]
- [inhales, sighs]

145
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,533
[tires screech]

146
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,912
- Hey! Are you okay?
- Huh?

147
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:57,583
Your boss jumped. We almost got shot.

148
00:06:58,126 --> 00:06:59,252
We almost crashed.

149
00:06:59,335 --> 00:07:01,087
[grunts] Oh.

150
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,922
[in English] I think I am okay. Yes.

151
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:05,591
You even decided to ride along!

152
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,969
I did not know you were
into deadly car chases!

153
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:10,179
Do you not know who we are following?

154
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:13,099
- [in English] No!
- Do you not know

155
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:14,058
what happened inside the bar?

156
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:15,852
[in English] No!
How would I know all that?

157
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,354
- Fool Batman!
- What?!

158
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,648
Your father was inside the bar.

159
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:23,526
Do you not know
the illegal activities happening there?

160
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:25,278
[in English] It was a coincidence.

161
00:07:25,361 --> 00:07:26,779
I do not even know why my dad was there!

162
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:29,740
Wait, why do you have so many questions?

163
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:31,742
You are not telling me
why you were there either.

164
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:36,581
[inquisitive music playing]

165
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:42,670
There they are.

166
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:51,262
- [Gavin sighs]
- You good there?

167
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:54,515
Come on! Get down!

168
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,684
- Huh?
- Get down!

169
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,562
Sir, there is still space in the back.

170
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:00,980
Get down!

171
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:05,860
[inquisitive music continues]

172
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,404
Come on.

173
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:10,615
Wait. You are leaving me here?

174
00:08:11,407 --> 00:08:12,283
Yes.

175
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,619
You are grown. You know how to get home.

176
00:08:14,702 --> 00:08:16,537
- [Atoy] Come on.
- [in English] Are you serious?!

177
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:20,166
[scoffs] No. I am joking.

178
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:23,169
[Atoy] Yes, that was just a joke.
What did you think, I was serious?

179
00:08:23,252 --> 00:08:24,212
[chuckles]

180
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:25,588
Here is another joke.

181
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:29,050
If you tell anyone about us,

182
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:33,679
I will slice your tongue,
then sew it to your forehead

183
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,265
before I kill you.

184
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:40,353
Come on.

185
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:51,197
[phone ringing]

186
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:53,658
[in English] Dad.

187
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:55,243
Where are you?

188
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,577
Mongki and I did not catch you.

189
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:57,912
[in English] I saw my friends.

190
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,205
I went with them.

191
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,874
Dad, what happened at the club?

192
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,209
Why did it suddenly turn chaotic?

193
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:06,087
Do not ask me anymore.
I do not know either.

194
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:09,465
What matters is you go home.
Your mom is looking for you.

195
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:13,803
[pensive music playing]

196
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:19,475
Why did you not wait for Gavin?

197
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:20,810
There was a shootout inside, right?

198
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,812
My child could have been hurt.

199
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,106
[in English] Sorry, Boss.

200
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:28,025
I was just thinking you might
have needed backup earlier.

201
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:31,112
I can handle myself.

202
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:33,447
That is right, Boss.

203
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:37,660
The only thing you could not handle
was the impostor you faced earlier.

204
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,372
That bastard.

205
00:09:41,455 --> 00:09:43,207
He ruined the plan.

206
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:48,004
I hope I see them again,
so I can make them crawl to hell.

207
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:52,883
[sirens wailing]

208
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:58,014
What can you say about the incident?

209
00:09:59,056 --> 00:10:02,893
[sobbing] That place is truly hell
for people like us.

210
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:06,230
[Tessie] <i>They treated us like toys.</i>

211
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:10,234
<i>They treated us like slaves.</i>

212
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,444
[sobbing]

213
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,406
[Tessie] <i>Our fight does not end here.</i>

214
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:16,824
I know that.

215
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,410
Sister Ame was taken to that bar.

216
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:22,121
[Tessie] <i>Those responsible</i>
<i>will answer for it.</i>

217
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,414
Oh my!

218
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:26,375
I thought you were going
to sleep earlier after we prayed?

219
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:29,003
I cannot sleep.

220
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:32,548
Let me see what you are watching.

221
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:36,135
[Tessie] <i>There must be justice…</i>

222
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:38,095
Where is Sister Ame?

223
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:39,555
[Tessie] <i>…for what happened to us.</i>

224
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,432
Why is Sister Ame not with her?

225
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:45,102
[Tessie] <i>Especially after one of us died!</i>

226
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:48,064
[Tessie] <i>We will fight!</i>

227
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:50,441
- [Tessie] <i>Right, we will fight?</i>
- Someone died?

228
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:52,777
- [Tessie] <i>We will fight.</i>
- Sister…

229
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,445
[stammers] What do you mean?

230
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:56,614
Your sister was with Endless Nights?

231
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,240
[Tessie] <i>We hope we get justice.</i>

232
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:02,244
- Master promised to save Sister.
- [Tessie] <i>Especially the death</i>

233
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:04,080
<i>of one of us.</i>

234
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,956
[sobbing] Sister Ame.

235
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,667
- [sobs]
- [shushes]

236
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:11,545
- [Tessie] <i>Have mercy on us.</i>
- [sobbing] Sister Ame.

237
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:16,217
[somber music playing]

238
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:21,889
- [sobbing]
- [Ame] Ibyang?

239
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,478
Sister Ame!

240
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,439
I am here.

241
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:32,817
It is okay. Calm down.

242
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,112
I watched it on the cellphone.

243
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:38,155
I thought you were gone.

244
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:43,077
[sobbing]

245
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:46,872
[gentle music playing]

246
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:56,006
Karla, just tell me already.

247
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,842
I just want to understand.

248
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:00,219
- Why did they save Ibyang’s sister?
- [unsettling music playing]

249
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:03,806
Is that their job?
Are they an undercover police officer?

250
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:06,934
Tonet, it really is not allowed.
Just ignore it.

251
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:09,812
No. I really cannot settle down.

252
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:11,355
I truly do not understand.

253
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,190
Did you not come from the club?

254
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:18,362
Then they even saved the little persons.

255
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:20,948
Then I saw on the news
that there was a shooting,

256
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:22,741
and then there was also a fire.

257
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:25,494
Was Atoy responsible for all of that?

258
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:27,037
You were with them too.

259
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:29,165
[suspicious music playing]

260
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,207
Well, because…

261
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,209
[Karla] Enough! I do not
want to talk anymore!

262
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:34,420
[Tonet] You really will not talk
because I will talk now.

263
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:37,047
I am smart. This girl is smart.

264
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:40,301
I know Atoy is not just a tailor.

265
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:47,349
Tonet, whatever you are thinking,

266
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:49,518
I just want you to know,

267
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,312
Atoy is not a bad person.

268
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:52,229
‪[pensive music playing]

269
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,191
[Cita] <i>He was formerly in the military.</i>

270
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:58,569
<i>That is where he trained</i>
<i>for a long time in combat.</i>

271
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:02,156
<i>One of his areas of expertise</i>
<i>is finding people.</i>

272
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:04,533
<i>And until now, he still uses that skill.</i>

273
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,870
I knew it.

274
00:13:07,953 --> 00:13:10,664
Atoy has another line of work
aside from tailoring.

275
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:14,210
He is like a tracker in disguise.

276
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:16,170
[in English] A secret tracker.

277
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:19,173
I am right, am I not?

278
00:13:19,256 --> 00:13:20,966
[Karla] That is exactly it.

279
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,552
So, if you want someone found,
whether a person or an object,

280
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,012
Brother Atoy is the man.

281
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,224
You did not tell me earlier.

282
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:32,061
Tonet, only Karla and I
know about that, okay?

283
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,896
Atoy’s job is difficult.

284
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:35,981
It is dangerous if other people find out.

285
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:38,734
I promise, Ms. Cita,

286
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:40,736
I will not tell anyone.
Even if it kills me.

287
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:44,156
Since I have already told you
and you already have an idea,

288
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:47,326
and you were already
part of Atoy’s mission.

289
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:51,330
The makeup.

290
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:54,500
So they would not be recognized
and could continue investigating.

291
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:55,668
[in English] Correct.

292
00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:57,044
You were really good at that.

293
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,504
I did not even recognize
Brother Atoy then.

294
00:13:58,587 --> 00:13:59,505
He looked old.

295
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,423
Still handsome though.

296
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:04,468
You know, even with makeup on,

297
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:06,136
his face shape was still beautiful.

298
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,472
You know, still handsome.

299
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:10,266
Makes you want to kiss him!

300
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,226
- [whimsical music playing]
- There she goes again.

301
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:14,353
You are really obsessed
with Brother Atoy, huh?

302
00:14:14,436 --> 00:14:16,146
Of course, that is my TTH.

303
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,690
TTH?

304
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:19,275
TTH.

305
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:22,987
As in they really are
the perfect example of TTH.

306
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,698
As in Tall, Tawny, Handsome.

307
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:27,825
And not just that.

308
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:32,079
- Mmm-hmm.
- And now a tailor slash secret tracker,

309
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:33,873
who is grumpy.

310
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,916
That is fine.

311
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,876
Still handsome anyway.

312
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:39,420
[in English] I love you, Atoy!

313
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:41,672
You are a fantasy. Fantasy!

314
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:43,132
- Oh, go on, give it.
- Harder. Harder.

315
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:45,259
- [snips]
- [clicking]

316
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:53,767
Ibyang, Atoy said they looked
for me because of you.

317
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,436
[somber music playing]

318
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:57,605
They were just being persistent with me.

319
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:04,194
And Ms. Cita really insisted
that they help me find you.

320
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:08,949
This kid never disappoints.

321
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:12,202
Ibyang, that does not seem right.

322
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:16,540
I mean, I owe my life to Atoy.

323
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,792
If not for him,

324
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:21,211
I would have been taken
by those foreigners.

325
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:22,880
Who knows where I would be now.

326
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:28,719
Do you want me to thank him?

327
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,931
Is that not what should be done?

328
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:36,018
[somber music playing]

329
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,190
- Master Grumpy.
- Mmm?

330
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:47,571
Thank you for keeping your promise

331
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,698
to bring back my Sister Ame.

332
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,116
Of course.

333
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:56,705
[in English] Well,
you are welcome, Little Miss Sassy.

334
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,500
[in English] Little Miss Sassy?

335
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:00,751
Mmm-hmm.

336
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:04,338
You do not want to call me
by my real name,

337
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:07,174
so I will call you that too.

338
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:08,759
You do not like that?

339
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:12,930
Do whatever you want.

340
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,558
We will not see each other again anyway.

341
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:20,980
Ibyang, what are you saying?

342
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,399
I have an agreement with Master Grumpy.

343
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:28,737
The moment I find you,
I will leave his house.

344
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:34,243
So, Master Grumpy, are you happy now?

345
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:35,577
- Well then.
- [scoffs]

346
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,454
[in English] To the infinite power.

347
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:43,127
[bright music playing]

348
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:55,597
Ibyang, do we really
have to leave right now?

349
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:58,851
I cannot take back what I said,
Sister Ame.

350
00:16:58,934 --> 00:17:02,646
Master might even call me out
for not keeping my word.

351
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:05,941
- It is already late.
- [gentle music playing]

352
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,485
Maybe you want to postpone it for now?

353
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:09,862
You can sleep here.

354
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,532
You can still do it tomorrow.

355
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:15,159
It really is not possible.

356
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:18,037
I will be embarrassed if we stay here.

357
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:22,041
Thank you for the offer,
but we really are going home.

358
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:23,834
[Ame] Go home where?

359
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,586
Ibyang, come on!

360
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:29,339
You would really rather go there,
to that old bus you said was flooded,

361
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:31,800
instead of this house with a bed?

362
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:35,387
I am already committed, Sister Ame.

363
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:37,014
There is no turning back.

364
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:38,932
Come on, Sister Ame.

365
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,395
All right, Atoy, we will go ahead now.

366
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:46,523
Thank you very much for saving my life.

367
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:49,610
All right.

368
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:51,695
Take care, okay?

369
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,323
[in English] Goodbye, Master Grumpy.

370
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:56,408
Thank you for all your help.

371
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:59,078
But I hope this is our last meeting.

372
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:00,913
Come on, Sister Ame.

373
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:08,670
That is my wish too, Little Miss Sassy.
Bye-bye.

374
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:12,591
Whoo.

375
00:18:12,674 --> 00:18:17,054
Finally, I have my house to myself.

376
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,098
[scoffs]

377
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:26,021
What did you and Atoy really argue about?

378
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,065
He seems like a good person.

379
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:32,736
He is not nice, Sister Ame.

380
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:33,987
I promise.

381
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:38,909
So, what is it?
What is the reason his blood boils

382
00:18:38,992 --> 00:18:40,828
whenever you face each other?

383
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,665
He is extremely grumpy.

384
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:47,668
He is the one being helped.

385
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,879
Yet he is the one getting angry.

386
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:55,551
Being helped?

387
00:18:56,593 --> 00:19:00,180
I cooked for him, and he got angry.

388
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:03,809
I cleaned, and he was angry too.

389
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:06,478
Bottom line, he is not nice.

390
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,898
That is why it is right
that we left his house.

391
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,443
[man] Hey, where are you going?

392
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:15,487
Oh, to the old terminal.

393
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:16,572
It is closed.

394
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:17,948
Entry is no longer allowed.

395
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:19,783
This is now private property.

396
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:21,910
What?

397
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:24,663
What about our home, Sister Ame?

398
00:19:24,746 --> 00:19:27,791
That was not really our home, Ibyang.

399
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:30,085
An abandoned bus.

400
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:32,045
Trash.

401
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:34,673
A real home is like the one Atoy has.

402
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:36,675
But I do not want to go there!

403
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,219
What are we going to do now?

404
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:42,264
We will be on the sidewalk again,
getting eaten by mosquitoes.

405
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:46,393
Even just one night, Ibyang,

406
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:50,272
that we can experience a bed
and a house with a roof.

407
00:19:56,528 --> 00:20:00,991
[serene music playing]

408
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:11,960
[grunts]

409
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:13,962
[sighs]

410
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,256
[sighs]

411
00:20:18,091 --> 00:20:19,384
[grunts]

412
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,555
[grunts]

413
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:26,141
[exhales]

414
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,644
[in English] Peace and quiet.

415
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:32,522
[serene music continues]

416
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:38,654
[sharp inhale]

417
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:42,115
[exhales]

418
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:46,286
[satisfied sigh]

419
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:49,039
No burnt food.

420
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:51,083
[Ibyang, in English]
Breakfast is almost ready.

421
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:53,085
- What is this?
- Tocino.

422
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:56,004
No broken faucet.

423
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,631
[water running]

424
00:20:57,714 --> 00:20:59,424
No flooded floor.

425
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:05,264
Aha!

426
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:07,933
[in English] It is life.

427
00:21:08,016 --> 00:21:09,559
[serene music continues]

428
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:10,936
[chuckles softly]

429
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:23,949
[serene music continues]

430
00:21:25,575 --> 00:21:26,994
[Atoy] Why is this open?

431
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,495
[gentle music continues]

432
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:31,331
Master, is this you when you were young?

433
00:21:31,915 --> 00:21:34,543
- Is this your father?
- What are you doing here?

434
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:36,753
Who told you to come in here?

435
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:40,966
Uh, sorry, Master.

436
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,343
- [Ibyang] Uh…
- Out!

437
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:48,432
[somber music playing]

438
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:06,992
[door squeaks]

439
00:22:08,535 --> 00:22:10,203
[Delfin] When I am gone,

440
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:13,290
do not turn my room into a museum.

441
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,544
You might not let anyone else use it.

442
00:22:17,627 --> 00:22:19,713
Dad, this is your room.

443
00:22:19,796 --> 00:22:22,299
No one else will ever use this.

444
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:24,885
See, that is exactly what I am saying.

445
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:30,682
You know, I will just be a soul by then.

446
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:33,435
I will not be using this anymore.

447
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:36,772
You know, when you have a child…

448
00:22:37,439 --> 00:22:38,482
A child?

449
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,193
I have no plans to get married.

450
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:42,611
What?

451
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:46,281
Do you want to grow old single?

452
00:22:46,364 --> 00:22:47,449
[scoffs]

453
00:22:47,532 --> 00:22:49,493
That does not suit you.

454
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,037
What a waste of a handsome man.

455
00:22:52,829 --> 00:22:56,541
Also, will you not continue our lineage?

456
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:59,920
I want you to have someone in life.

457
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:02,255
Well, there is.

458
00:23:02,339 --> 00:23:05,801
You are there, and Ms. Cita is there.

459
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:09,638
Cita has another family.

460
00:23:11,139 --> 00:23:14,142
When I am gone, you will be alone.

461
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:21,817
I am used to being alone.

462
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:28,323
I also got used to it when you left me.

463
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:33,036
But that does not mean I enjoyed it.

464
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,122
[somber music continues]

465
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:44,256
[sewing machine clicks open]

466
00:23:49,886 --> 00:23:52,556
I thought you did not want to come back--

467
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:56,101
- Godmother!
- [Cita] Who are you talking to?

468
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:58,145
[in English] Morning. Good morning.

469
00:23:58,228 --> 00:24:00,355
- Ah, good morning.
- Ah…

470
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:03,191
No one.

471
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:04,317
Ah.

472
00:24:05,026 --> 00:24:08,613
Karla said you already
rescued Ibyang’s sister.

473
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:12,242
I checked your house early this morning,
but I did not catch them.

474
00:24:13,076 --> 00:24:14,286
Well…

475
00:24:15,579 --> 00:24:16,621
Well, they…

476
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:19,124
They insisted on leaving,

477
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:20,667
so they left.

478
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,335
You did not even stop them?

479
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:23,712
I stopped them.

480
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:26,047
You can even ask them.

481
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:26,965
[chuckles]

482
00:24:27,048 --> 00:24:30,135
How can I ask
when the sisters are already gone?

483
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:36,600
Oh. You give this to Ibyang, okay?

484
00:24:38,435 --> 00:24:39,811
What is this, Godmother?

485
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:42,731
The clothes of hers that I washed.

486
00:24:45,775 --> 00:24:48,570
Godmother, I am already busy.

487
00:24:48,653 --> 00:24:50,363
I need to return to my real work.

488
00:24:50,447 --> 00:24:52,824
The people I am searching for,
there is still

489
00:24:52,908 --> 00:24:54,242
one important thing to do.

490
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:55,869
I cannot do that anymore.

491
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,579
Come on, Atoy.

492
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:01,541
I am sure that Ibyang will not come
back here because of fear of you,

493
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:04,544
because of your agreement
that when you rescued her sister,

494
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:06,504
you would forget each other.
That is what you said, right?

495
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:10,675
There you go. Then let us
just give it to another child.

496
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:12,427
Or just leave it here.

497
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:14,804
We can make rags out of it or whatever.

498
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:16,097
Huh?

499
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:19,851
There are only a few pieces
of the child’s clothes.

500
00:25:20,894 --> 00:25:22,062
Come on.

501
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:24,105
Do not let your pride take over.

502
00:25:24,189 --> 00:25:25,899
You go to her yourself.

503
00:25:28,026 --> 00:25:29,361
[groans]

504
00:25:29,444 --> 00:25:30,612
[Cita] Mmm?

505
00:25:31,947 --> 00:25:32,948
All right!

506
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:35,450
Thank you.

507
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:36,868
No. I am really busy.

508
00:25:36,952 --> 00:25:38,370
That is fine.

509
00:25:52,634 --> 00:25:55,262
[inquisitive music continues]

510
00:26:04,854 --> 00:26:05,730
Boss.

511
00:26:07,565 --> 00:26:10,235
I was heading toward the terminal area.

512
00:26:10,318 --> 00:26:11,444
Oh?

513
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:12,821
Is there no other route?

514
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:14,823
No one lives there anymore.

515
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:16,908
- We were forced to leave.
- Forced out?

516
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,576
Yes. After the flood,

517
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,287
the owner took advantage
and fenced it off,

518
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:21,663
so we could not return anymore.

519
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:23,540
I am actually looking for someone.

520
00:26:23,623 --> 00:26:26,543
Two women, uh…

521
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,712
kids.

522
00:26:28,795 --> 00:26:29,671
They are sisters.

523
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:31,131
Ibyang and Ame.

524
00:26:31,214 --> 00:26:33,591
Ah, Ame. The small girl?

525
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:35,385
That is her. Do you know them?

526
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:37,387
I have not seen them, Bro.

527
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:38,847
It has been a long time since we last met.

528
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:41,975
She even still owes me money.
Until now, it has not been paid.

529
00:26:42,058 --> 00:26:43,310
Oh, how much?

530
00:26:43,393 --> 00:26:44,519
Fifty.

531
00:26:44,602 --> 00:26:45,520
Thousand?

532
00:26:45,603 --> 00:26:47,647
No. Just 50 pesos.

533
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:52,944
[inquisitive music continues]

534
00:26:54,070 --> 00:26:55,613
All right. Wait.

535
00:26:57,532 --> 00:26:59,284
I will give you ten times that

536
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:01,244
if you can point me
to where I can find them.

537
00:27:02,579 --> 00:27:04,289
[in English] Hey, times ten.

538
00:27:04,372 --> 00:27:05,665
All right, all right. Let us do this.

539
00:27:05,749 --> 00:27:06,958
I will call my friends,

540
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:08,251
so we can easily find Ame.

541
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:10,670
That’s it. That how it should be.

542
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,631
- It is up to you, Boss.
- All right.

543
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:14,716
Okay.

544
00:27:16,259 --> 00:27:18,845
[dials beeping]

545
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:20,430
[line rings]

546
00:27:20,513 --> 00:27:21,890
[vendor] Hello, friend.

547
00:27:21,973 --> 00:27:23,475
[stirring music playing]

548
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:26,561
[electronic blipping]

549
00:27:31,566 --> 00:27:33,651
Just text me if you need a retouch.

550
00:27:33,735 --> 00:27:35,862
Or if you need company.

551
00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:37,739
- So, Ame? Game?
- Game.

552
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:39,616
- [cheering]
- [in English] Hi, kids!

553
00:27:39,699 --> 00:27:41,785
- [male kid] Hi!
- [chuckles]

554
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:44,204
UP NEXT

555
00:27:46,456 --> 00:27:49,000
I will bring you back to your boss.

556
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:52,670
[Dmitri, in English] <i>He can find anything</i>
<i>or anyone on this earth.</i>

557
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:53,755
[in English] Master Cutter?

558
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:55,256
Do you want someone found?

559
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:56,925
[in English] Someone from my past.

560
00:27:57,008 --> 00:27:57,967
[in English] My daughter is here.

561
00:27:58,051 --> 00:28:00,553
Looks like someone else
wants to ask for help too.

562
00:28:00,637 --> 00:28:01,554
[in English] Dad.

563
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:07,727
[music intensifies]

564
00:28:10,688 --> 00:28:12,357
Subtitle translation by: Judy Galleta
